=== Investigation (E4 diagnosis) ===

Compared physics-lint/src/physics_lint/rules/ph_res_001.py against
diffusion-physics/src/diffphys/evaluation/metrics.py::pde_residual_norm:

  Aspect       physics-lint                 upstream
  --------     -------------------------    -------------------------
  Stencil      fd4 (4th-order, via         fd2 5-point
               field.laplacian, cached)     (f[i-1] + f[i+1] + f[j-1]
                                             + f[j+1] - 4*f[i,j]) / h²
  Scope        full 64x64 grid             interior 62x62 only
               (boundary stencil reaches    (indices [1:-1, 1:-1])
               into ghost cells)
  Norm         L² trapezoidal quadrature   RMS (dimensionless mean
               sqrt(∫|r|² dA), i.e.        of squared interior
               sqrt(sum_weighted * h²)      residuals, then sqrt)

Scale ratios (physlint / upstream): DDPM 5.53x, UNet 1.65x, FNO 1.35x.
Consistent direction (physlint always higher) matches the scope +
norm difference.

Discretization-parameter audit (plan E4 checklist):
  h: (1/63, 1/63) both sides — match ✓
  periodic: False (correct for Laplace Dirichlet) ✓
  backend: fd (as spec declares) ✓
  field shape: (64, 64) float32 ✓

No discretization bug. The BUG verdict is produced mechanically by
compute_verdict(sanity_match=False) but the root cause is the
documented §6.5 "not a 1:1 reimplementation" gap (different stencil
order, different scope, different norm). At reduced-scope n=100,
UNet/FNO differ by 3% in physlint vs 19% in upstream — plausibly
within sampling variance at reduced n.

PH-POS-002 binary mismatch: physlint threshold 1e-10 vs upstream's
1e-6 (§6.5 threshold-mismatch case). FNO's upstream max_viol=0.006
represents a small interior overshoot that physlint's stricter
threshold would have caught, but the raw PH-POS-002 value is 0.0 for
all three models — this suggests upstream's "overshoot count" and
physlint's "overshoot magnitude" differ in definition, not only
threshold. Aggregation reports 0 violators where 1 was expected.

