=== Reconsidered outcome (~13:30Z): PASS (scoped, MIXED) ===

On review (user-initiated, before the branch was pushed), the E4
reading was recognized as firing the plan's machinery against its
intent. The plan's E4 branch was written for a specific failure
mode — "physics-lint's L² disagrees with upstream's L² on the same
quantity → discretization bug in one implementation" — and assumed
the sanity axis was a byte-identical comparison. Design doc §6.5
had already disclosed it wasn't: PH-RES-001 and upstream
pde_residual_norm deliberately differ on stencil order (fd4 vs
fd2), scope (full-grid vs interior-only), and norm (L² trapezoidal
vs dimensionless RMS). Firing BUG on a pre-disclosed property is a
verdict-rule design flaw (the §7 rule should have softened BUG to
INCOMPARABLE for the definitional-gap case), not a discovered
discretization bug.

Applying the plan's intent rather than its machinery, the three
axes produced three distinct outcomes:

  sanity  PH-RES-001 vs pde_residual    INCOMPARABLE — rank-1 (DDPM)
          agrees; rank-2/3 swap within plausible sampling variance
          at n=100 (3% physlint separation vs 19% upstream).
  real    PH-BC-001  vs bc_err          MATCH — full-ranking
          agreement on 3 ML surrogates; magnitudes in directionally-
          consistent proportions (L² rel vs L¹ abs, ~2-7× higher).
  real    PH-POS-002 vs max_viol        DEFINITIONAL GAP — quantity
          disagreement (magnitude vs count), not ranking
          disagreement. Models too tight to the BC envelope for
          physlint's 1e-10 magnitude floor to trip.

Net: Criterion 3 met in scoped form on 3 real ML surrogates.
Scoping has more dimensions than "n=3 models": the sanity axis is
incomparable-by-definitional-gap with rank-1 consistency only, one
real axis is fully MATCH, the other real axis is a definitional
gap whose resolution is v1.1 work (metrics-compatibility shim —
see docs/backlog/v1.1.md 2026-04-17 entry).

Action taken: git reset --soft HEAD~2 to un-commit both the Bucket I
commit and the fourth-round tradeoffs revision (both local-only,
never pushed). Reconstructed dogfood_real_results.md with the
PASS (scoped, MIXED) framing; fifth-round tradeoffs revisions
written to match. Single recommit lands infrastructure + verdict
file + fifth-round docs together.

=== Process lesson ===

Tripwires that route to "commit as X" under time pressure should
route to "pause and interpret, then commit as whatever
interpretation lands" — not straight to the commit. The 5-10
minutes of interpretation time before `git commit` is cheap
insurance against mechanical rule-firing overwriting actual
findings. In this case, the interpretive question ("is this a
real discretization bug or a pre-flagged definitional gap?") was
the actual work; the escape-matrix lookup was machinery that
fired before the interpretation completed.
